---

## Core Scripts

### 1. Training — [faces-train.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/faces-train.py)

Builds the face recognition model:

1. Walks [images/](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/timelapse.py#41-53) directory — each sub-folder name becomes a **label**
2. Converts images to grayscale, resizes to 550×550
3. Runs Haar cascade detection to extract face ROIs
4. Trains an **LBPH recognizer** with the detected faces
5. Saves the model → [recognizers/face-trainner.yml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/recognizers/face-trainner.yml) and labels → [pickles/face-labels.pickle](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/pickles/face-labels.pickle)

### 2. Recognition — [faces.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/faces.py)

The main application with **5 different modes** (only one is active, rest are commented out):

| Mode | Lines | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| Live webcam recognition | 1–73 | Detect + recognize faces on live video |
| Static image recognition | 77–135 | Detect + recognize faces from an image file |
| Long-distance live | 138–208 | Live mode with adjusted params for distant faces |
| **Save-and-process (ACTIVE)** | **213–297** | Captures frame → saves → reloads → detects → recognizes |
| Streamlined live | 311–379 | Simplified live capture + recognition loop |

**Active mode** captures each webcam frame, saves it as [full_frame_live.png](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/full_frame_live.png), reloads it, runs face detection (confidence range 4–85), labels recognized faces, draws blue rectangles, and saves cropped faces as [detected_face.png](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/detected_face.png).

### 3. Alt Detection — [Face_detect.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/Face_detect.py)

Uses the `face_recognition` library (dlib-based) for comparing face encodings between images followed by a live detection loop using `SimpleFacerec`.

> [!WARNING]
> This script has structural issues: `SimpleFacerec` is used before it's imported (line 16 vs 20), and images referenced (`Messi1.webp`, `images/Messi.webp`) aren't present in the repo.

---

## Video Effects & Utilities

| Script | What it does |
|--------|-------------|
| [filter.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py) | Applies 6 live camera filters: hue/saturation, sepia, color overlay, invert, circle blur, portrait mode |
| [glasses_and_stash.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/glasses_and_stash.py) | AR overlay — detects eyes & nose via cascades, overlays glasses.png and mustache.png |
| [watermark.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/watermark.py) | Adds a semi-transparent logo watermark to the bottom-right of live video |
| [timelapse.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/timelapse.py) | Captures frames every 0.25s for 20s, then stitches them into a video |
| [record.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/record.py) | Simple webcam video recorder (720p, AVI) |
| [res-change.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/res-change.py) | Demonstrates resolution scaling (30% and 500%) |
| [base.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/base.py) | Minimal camera capture loop |
| [camera-test.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/camera-test.py) | Shows color + grayscale feed side-by-side |

---

## Utility Module — [utils.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/utils.py)

- **[image_resize(image, width, height)](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/utils.py#5-31)** — Aspect-ratio-preserving resize
- **[CFEVideoConf](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/utils.py#34-81)** class — Manages video capture resolution (360p–4K) and codec selection (XVID for AVI/MP4)

---

## How to Run

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies
pip install numpy opencv-contrib-python Pillow

# 2. Train the model (from src/ directory)
cd src
python faces-train.py

# 3. Run face recognition
python faces.py          # Press 'q' to quit

# 4. Try other scripts
python filter.py         # Live filters
python glasses_and_stash.py  # AR glasses & mustache
```

> [!NOTE]
> All scripts use `cv2.VideoCapture(0)` — your default webcam. If you have multiple cameras, change the index.

---

## Notable Observations

1. **Outdated dependencies** — [requirements.txt](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/requirements.txt) pins very old versions (numpy 1.14, opencv 3.4, Python 3.6). Modern Python 3.10+ and OpenCV 4.x are recommended.
2. **[faces.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/faces.py) is mostly commented out** — It contains 5 different approach iterations. Only the "save-and-process" loop (lines 213–297) is active.
3. **[Face_detect.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/Face_detect.py) has code order issues** — `SimpleFacerec()` is called before the import, and referenced images don't exist in the repo.
4. **Training images included** — GoT actors (Emilia Clarke, Kit Harington, etc.) plus your own photos in `Jk/` and `jk2/`.
5. **Pre-trained model exists** — [face-trainner.yml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/recognizers/face-trainner.yml) (6.9 MB) is ready to use without retraining.
